== 偵測 ==
偵測亞甲基二氧吡咯戊酮和其他合成性卡西酮化合物相當困難，這些毒品的化合物可逃過[[嗅探犬|嗅探犬]]的嗅覺偵測<ref name="CBC">{{Cite news|title=What are 'bath salts'? A look at Canada's newest illegal drug|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/what-are-bath-salts-a-look-at-canada-s-newest-illegal-drug-1.1143407|date=25 June 2012|author=Black|first=Matthew|publisher=[[Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|work=[[CBC_News|CBC News]]|accessdate=28 December 2013}}</ref>，一般的[[尿液分析|尿液分析]]也無法偵測。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Are "Bath Salts" the next generation of stimulant abuse?|url=|last=Winder|first=G. S.|last2=Stern|first2=N.|date=March 2012|journal=J Subst Abuse Treat|issue=1|doi=10.1016/j.jsat.2012.02.003|volume=44|pages=42–45|pmid=22445773|last3=Hosanagar|first3=A.}}</ref> 但可用透過尿液和毛髮使用[[氣相色譜法-質譜聯用|氣相色譜法-質譜聯用]]（Gas chromatography–mass spectrometry） 或[[液相色譜法-質譜聯用|液相色譜法-質譜聯用]]（Liquid chromatography-mass spectrometry），兩者物質色譜法-質譜聯用皆可偵測出浴鹽化合物。<ref>{{Cite book|last=Baselt|first=R.|url=http://www.biomedicalpublications.com/mephedrone.pdf|title=Disposition of Toxic Drugs and Chemicals in Man|edition=11th|publisher=Biomedical Publications|location=Seal Beach, CA|year=2017|pages=1280–1282|accessdate=29 June 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425083904/http://www.biomedicalpublications.com/mephedrone.pdf|archivedate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Prevalence of new psychoactive substances: A retrospective study in hair|journal=Drug Testing and Analysis|issue=6|doi=10.1002/dta.1338|year=2012|volume=4|pages=402–408|pmc=|pmid=22522922}}</ref> 毒販可能會將該毒品偽裝成[[肥料|肥料]]、[[驅蟲劑|驅蟲劑]]和[[洗衣膠囊|洗衣膠囊]]等日常用化學產品使檢驗儀器混淆或無法分辨逃過檢測。<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsday.com/news/new-york/bath-salts-synthetic-drugs-targeted-in-schneiderman-lawsuits-1.3829630|title='Bath salts,' synthetic drugs targeted in Schneiderman lawsuits|publisher=Long Island Newsday|date=10 July 2012|accessdate=18 December 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131228075413/http://www.newsday.com/news/new-york/bath-salts-synthetic-drugs-targeted-in-schneiderman-lawsuits-1.3829630|archivedate=28 December 2013|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->}}</ref>

== 盛行率 ==
對於到底有多少人使用浴鹽所知甚少。<ref name="coppola">{{Cite journal|title=Synthetic cathinones: Chemistry, pharmacology and toxicology of a new class of designer drugs of abuse marketed as "bath salts" or "plant food"|journal=Toxicology Letters|issue=2|doi=10.1016/j.toxlet.2012.03.009|year=2012|volume=211|pages=144–149|pmc=|pmid=22459606}}</ref> 在英國含有甲氧麻黃酮的浴鹽是第四普遍非法用於夜店的毒品，僅次於[[大麻|大麻]]、 [[MDMA|MDMA]]類毒品和古柯鹼。 根據[[美國毒物控制中心協會|美國毒物控制中心協會]]報告統計，美國浴鹽使用率在2010–2011年之間有顯著的上升。 該毒品在那段時期使用率顯著增加，有推測可能是該毒品的具有多項優勢，便宜、高度上癮性、青少年與年輕人想找刺激與新鮮感上的尋求產生的需求、夜店對於毒品較快的汰舊換新，因而使用非常的廣泛。該藥物更能使使用者在強制性[[藥物測試|藥物測試]]中無法檢測而逃過檢測造成法律漏洞，這項優勢更使得浴鹽使用率更進一步的上升。<ref name="prosser">{{Cite journal|title=The Toxicology of Bath Salts: A Review of Synthetic Cathinones|journal=Journal of Medical Toxicology|issue=1|doi=10.1007/s13181-011-0193-z|year=2011|volume=8|pages=33–42|pmc=3550219|pmid=22108839}}</ref>

使用者年齡範圍約15–55歲，平均使用者年齡約28歲。<ref name="ask the doc">{{Cite web|title=Ask the Doctor: Bath salts—a new way to get high?|url=http://www.health.harvard.edu/newsletters/Harvard_Mental_Health_Letter/2011/September|accessdate=18 December 2013|author=Miller, Michael C.|date=September 2011|work=Harvard Mental Health Letter|quote=<br />Q. I heard a news story about people using bath salts to get high. How is that possible? My husband and I have two teenagers. Should we talk with them about this?<br /><br />A. The "bath salts" you've heard about have nothing to do with the type that people add to water and use while soaking in a tub. These newer bath salts are designer drugs that circumvent the laws governing controlled or illegal substances, but can be used to get high.<br /><br />The active chemicals in these salts — mephedrone, pyrovalerone, or methylenedioxypyrovalerone (MDPV) — all have stimulant properties. They are ...}} {{Linknote|note=contains additional text}}</ref>

== 法律狀態 ==
2012年秋季以來加拿大已將亞甲基二氧吡咯戊酮（Methylenedioxypyrovalerone, MDPV），根據《[[受管制藥物與物質法令|受管制藥物與物質法令]]》（Controlled Drugs and Substances Act）列為第一級管制藥物，跟MDMA類毒品和海洛因同分類。<ref name="CBC">{{Cite news|title=What are 'bath salts'? A look at Canada's newest illegal drug|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/what-are-bath-salts-a-look-at-canada-s-newest-illegal-drug-1.1143407|date=25 June 2012|author=Black|first=Matthew|publisher=[[Canadian_Broadcasting_Corporation|Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|work=[[CBC_News|CBC News]]|accessdate=28 December 2013}}</ref> 甲氧麻黃酮和亞甲基雙氧甲基卡西酮已在加拿大和美國大多數州列管非法藥物 。

在[[1971年毒品濫用法|1971年毒品濫用法]] （Misuse of Drugs Act 1971）法案下，英國將所有[[卡西酮衍生物|卡西酮衍生物]]在2010年4月列為非法藥物，<ref name="bbc0704">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/house_of_commons/newsid_8605000/8605939.stm|title=BBC – Democracy Live – MPs move to ban mephedrone|publisher=BBC News|date=7 April 2010|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-date=2018-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180705093329/http://news.bbc.co.uk/democracylive/hi/house_of_commons/newsid_8605000/8605939.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="opsi.gov">{{Cite news|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2010/1144/made|title=The Misuse of Drugs (Amendment) (England, Wales and Scotland) Regulations 2010 No. 1144|publisher=Office of Public Sector Information|date=16 April 2010|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5wOiOGPha?url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2010/1144/made|archivedate=10 February 2011}}</ref> ，但其他狡詐家藥物如[[萘菲酮|萘菲酮]] （Naphyrone）不久後出現 ，有些標示為合法的藥物含有非法毒品化合物。<ref name="bbc1207">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10602398|title=NRG-1 'legal high' drug is banned|publisher=BBC News|date=12 July 2010|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020120535/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/10602398|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="brandt">{{Cite journal|title=Second generation mephedrone: The confusing case of NRG-1|last=Brandt|first=SD|last2=Sumnall|first2=HR|date=July 2010|journal=British Medical Journal|issue=|doi=10.1136/bmj.c3564|volume=341|pages=c3564|pmid=20605894|last3=Measham|first3=F|last4=Cole|first4=J}}</ref> 為躲過[[1968年藥品法|藥品法]]的管轄監控，一些毒品如甲氧麻黃酮以“浴鹽”之名， 或以名稱標記不當如“植物性食品”規避，這些毒品以這些方式鑽法律漏洞，出現在英國市面上販售。<ref name="reed1301">{{Cite news|author=Reed|first=Jim|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/hi/health/newsid_10000000/newsid_10004300/10004366.stm|title=Clubbers are 'turning to new legal high mephedrone'|publisher=BBC News|date=13 January 2010|accessdate=4 July 2010|archive-date=2010-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100116034643/http://news.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/hi/health/newsid_10000000/newsid_10004300/10004366.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="acmdreport">{{Cite web|title=Consideration of the Cathinones|url=http://drugs.homeoffice.gov.uk/publication-search/acmd/ACMD-cathinones-report.pdf|accessdate=1 April 2010|date=31 March 2010|publisher=Advisory Council on the Misuse of Drugs|archiveurl=http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20100402214933/http%3A//drugs.homeoffice.gov.uk/publication%2Dsearch/acmd/ACMD%2Dcathinones%2Dreport.pdf|archivedate=2 April 2010}}</ref><ref name="bbc2711">{{Cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/tees/8370130.stm|title=Police warning over 'bubble' drug|date=20 November 2009|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224145043/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/england/tees/8370130.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2015年3月採用[[聯合國麻醉藥品委員會|聯合國麻醉藥品委員會]] （United Nations Commission on Narcotic Drugs）的法案加強管制，將浴鹽歸類新興影響精神物質（New psychoactive substances，NPS），退止對人民造成健康危害。

2012年7月美國修正《[[聯邦食品、藥品和化妝品法案|聯邦食品、藥品和化妝品法案]]》（Federal Food,Drug,and Cosmetic Act）加強藥物控制政策禁止含浴鹽化合物並以“浴鹽”之名出現在容器及包裝。此前美國有41州將浴鹽列為合法藥物，連同這些浴鹽成份的化合物也曾合法。<ref name="Obama">{{Cite news|url=http://newsfeed.time.com/2012/07/10/obama-signs-federal-ban-on-bath-salt-drugs/|title=Obama Signs Federal Ban on 'Bath Salt' Drugs|author=Patience Haggin|publisher=Newsfeed|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=10 July 2012|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129015516/https://newsfeed.time.com/2012/07/10/obama-signs-federal-ban-on-bath-salt-drugs/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ncsl.org/research/civil-and-criminal-justice/synthetic-drug-threats.aspx|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|title=Synthetic Drug Threats|publisher=National Conference of State Legislatures|date=28 November 2012|accessdate=28 December 2013|archive-date=2020-12-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201206164925/https://www.ncsl.org/research/civil-and-criminal-justice/synthetic-drug-threats.aspx|dead-url=no}}</ref>這種以“浴鹽”之名去通過合法藥物管制的方法遊走在《[[聯邦類似法|聯邦類似法]]》（Federal Analogue Act）的法律邊緣在這時都成定罪，禁止販售歸類於和人類使用藥物相似的毒品。<ref name="nyt">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/17/us/17salts.html|title=An Alarming New Stimulant, Legal in Many States|work=New York Times|author=Abby Goodnough|author2=Katie Zezima|date=16 July 2011|accessdate=15 January 2012|archive-date=2021-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210415032427/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/17/us/17salts.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.al.com/breaking/2011/02/synthetic_form_of_cocaine_and.html|title=Synthetic form of cocaine and methamphetamine being packaged as bath salts|publisher=The Huntsville Times|author=Victoria Cumbow|date=6 February 2011|accessdate=10 February 2011|archive-date=2011-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707102151/http://blog.al.com/breaking/2011/02/synthetic_form_of_cocaine_and.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Reports: Miami 'zombie' attacker may have been using 'bath salts'|url=http://news.blogs.cnn.com/2012/05/29/reports-miami-zombie-attacker-may-have-been-using-bath-salts|accessdate=28 December 2013|date=29 May 2012|publisher=CNN|archive-date=2021-03-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210325054706/https://news.blogs.cnn.com/2012/05/29/reports-miami-zombie-attacker-may-have-been-using-bath-salts/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

該毒品在已於[[台灣|台灣]]被列為[[準二級毒品|準二級毒品]]。

== 社群和媒體 ==
浴鹽的使用也透過社群媒體傳播，<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/aug/17/surge-in-monkey-dust-drug-use-linked-to-social-media-police-say|title=Surge in monkey dust drug use linked to social media, police say|author=Marsh|first=Sarah|date=2018-08-17|work=The Guardian|accessdate=2019-02-08|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109043144/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/aug/17/surge-in-monkey-dust-drug-use-linked-to-social-media-police-say|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在英國，軼事流傳該藥物降低了使用者的痛苦閾值並提升他們強度，很大程度上歸因於緊急服務和前線[[國民保健署|國民保健署]]（National Health Service, NHS）人員。透過地區新聞和小報刊等小型媒體報導，這些報導曾引起這些地區不小的轟動<ref>{{Cite web|title=The Truth About 'Monkey Dust', UK Media's Latest Drug Obsession|url=https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/pawwq7/monkey-dust-the-uks-latest-nightmare-drug-is-not-what-media-says-it-is|accessdate=2019-02-08|author=Daly|date=2018-08-16|first=Max|work=Vice|language=en|archive-date=2020-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200920061125/https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/pawwq7/monkey-dust-the-uks-latest-nightmare-drug-is-not-what-media-says-it-is|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/08/15/monkey-dust-warning-police-say-increasingly-popular-drug-leading/|title=Monkey dust warning as police say increasingly popular drug is leading to people jumping off buildings|author=Johnson|first=Jamie|date=2018-08-15|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=2019-02-08|language=en-GB|issn=0307-1235|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109025641/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/08/15/monkey-dust-warning-police-say-increasingly-popular-drug-leading/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在[[斯托克|斯托克]]，有報導指出該毒品是“全新”的化合物，事實上該毒品裡的化學物質早在1920年代就合成了，但直到2000年代初這些化學物質在才在市面上現身。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Neuropharmacology of 3,4-Methylenedioxypyrovalerone (MDPV), Its Metabolites, and Related Analogs|last=Baumann|first=Michael H.|last2=Bukhari|first2=Mohammad O.|date=2017|journal=Current Topics in Behavioral Neurosciences|doi=10.1007/7854_2016_53|volume=32|pages=93–117|isbn=978-3-319-52442-9|issn=1866-3370|pmc=5392131|pmid=27830575|last3=Lehner|first3=Kurt R.|last4=Anizan|first4=Sebastien|last5=Rice|first5=Kenner C.|last6=Concheiro|first6=Marta|last7=Huestis|first7=Marilyn A.}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Monkey dust couple's warning before setting their house on fire|url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/news/stoke-on-trent-news/theres-people-coming-us-what-2157927|accessdate=2019-02-08|author=Davies|date=2018-11-20|first=Ruby|work=stokesentinel|archive-date=2020-10-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001055827/https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/news/stoke-on-trent-news/theres-people-coming-us-what-2157927|dead-url=no}}</ref>  媒體經常使用文本框架技術來報導最易受傷害社會的合成性卡西酮。<ref>{{Cite web|title=How Broadcast Media Discuss New Drug "Epidemics": Integrating Neuroscience With Communication Studies Through Textual Framing - SAGE Research Methods|url=http://methods.sagepub.com/case/media-drug-epidemics-neuroscience-communication-studies-textual-framing|accessdate=2019-02-08|work=methods.sagepub.com|language=en|archive-date=2020-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200127054507/http://methods.sagepub.com/case/media-drug-epidemics-neuroscience-communication-studies-textual-framing|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2018年8月[[史丹佛郡|史丹佛郡]]警察隊曾收到十通關於浴鹽的電話。然而並沒有交代這些事件是否為浴鹽引起的，或由化合物組合而成的物質。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Monkey Dust mayhem: the English city reportedly at the centre of a drug-fuelled 'epidemic'|url=http://theconversation.com/monkey-dust-mayhem-the-english-city-reportedly-at-the-centre-of-a-drug-fuelled-epidemic-102066|accessdate=2019-02-08|author=Page|first=Sarah|work=The Conversation|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200813145722/https://theconversation.com/monkey-dust-mayhem-the-english-city-reportedly-at-the-centre-of-a-drug-fuelled-epidemic-102066|dead-url=no}}</ref>

浴鹽最初只有研究用之途，為[[研究用化學物質|研究用化學物質]]。在成為狡詐家藥物後，非娛樂用途之用的使用者為了研究該毒品的強度及毒性會在網路上購買相關化學物質，將其攝入後在部落格發布其造成的效果的文章。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/jul/04/psychonauts-drugs-experiment-chemistry-legal-highs|title=Psychonauts explore unknown world of legal highs – with themselves as lab rats|author=Boseley|first=Sarah|date=2014-07-04|work=The Guardian|accessdate=2019-02-08|author2=editor|first2=health|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2021-02-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210202070407/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2014/jul/04/psychonauts-drugs-experiment-chemistry-legal-highs|dead-url=no}}</ref>

